  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rohingya Refugee Crisis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	This project is one of several continuing ADRA&#x2019;s response to the crisis
&#x2022;	Working with UNHCR to provide assistance to infrastructure, shelters, and site management
&#x2022;	Will provide emergency shelter assistance to 10,000 families living in refugee camps
&#x2022;	Will provide camp management and site improvements for more than 12,000 households living in refugee camps over six months</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	We are responding to the Rohingya refugee crisis in Bangladesh where there are currently over 688,000 new arrivals from Myanmar since August 25, 2017
&#x2022;	On August 25 2017 there was renewed violence leading to roughly 500,000 civilians fleeing across the border from Myanmar to Bangladesh, all within a two week window.
&#x2022;	The rapid influx has tripled the population living in the existing camps, triggering the creation of several spontaneous settlements where people are seeking shelter, water, food items and sanitation facilities and struggling for basic survival need.</narrative>
  </description>
